text: The 1974 Atlantic hurricane season began on June 1, 1974 and ended on November 30, 1974. This season was about average in activity 11 storms, 7 of which got named. This season was one of the deadliest on record, most deaths were caused by Hurricane Fifi. This season also had the most Subtropical storms (4). ==Storms== *Subtropical Storm One *Subtropical Storm Two *Subtropical Storm Three *Tropical Storm Alma *Hurricane Becky *Hurricane Carmen *Tropical Storm Dolly *Tropical Storm Elaine *Hurricane Fifi *Hurricane Gertrude *Subtropical Storm Four ==Unused names== * * * * * * * * * * * * * * ==Retirement== In 1975 the names Carmen and Fifi were retired. ==Other websites== * HPC rainfall page for 1974 tropical cyclones * Monthly Weather Review 1974 Atlantic hurricane season Category:1970s in weather
